<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Universal_Life_Church&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: North Carolina">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">North Carolina</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/LynchvULC.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/LynchvULC.pdf" rel="nofollow">Lynch v. Universal Life Church (North Carolina)</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(7.62&#160;<a href="/wiki/Mebibyte" title="Mebibyte">MiB</a>)</span> (10/1985) Individual accuses ULC of fraud; church wins in district court.</li>
<li><span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/fultonvvickery.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/fultonvvickery.pdf" rel="nofollow">Fulton v. Vickery (North Carolina)</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(22.2&#160;<a href="/wiki/Kibibyte" title="Kibibyte">KiB</a>)</span> (03/1985) Marriage by ULC minister upheld since marriage occurred prior to <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1981-07-03"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="07-03"><a href="/wiki/July_3" title="July 3">July 3</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1981" title="1981">1981</a></span> (see NC § 51-1.1)</li>
<li><span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/NCvLynch.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/NCvLynch.pdf" rel="nofollow">State of North Carolina v. Lynch</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(8.00&#160;<a href="/wiki/Mebibyte" title="Mebibyte">MiB</a>)</span> (12/1980) State convicts person married by ULC minister of <a href="/wiki/Bigamy" title="Bigamy">bigamy</a> in second marriage, then overturned on appeal due to the marriage by the ULC minister being found as not a legal marriage.</li>
<li>ULC marriages prior to <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1981-07-03"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="07-03"><a href="/wiki/July_3" title="July 3">July 3</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1981" title="1981">1981</a></span> are validated. (NC § 51-1.1.) Marriages solemized after <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1981-07-03"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="07-03"><a href="/wiki/July_3" title="July 3">July 3</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1981" title="1981">1981</a></span> are questionable in legality due to the above case law</li>
</ul>
