<li><span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/RanierivRanieri.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/RanierivRanieri.pdf" rel="nofollow">Ranieri v Ranieri (New York State)</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(11.4&#160;<a href="/wiki/Mebibyte" title="Mebibyte">MiB</a>)</span> Marriage annulled on basis that ULC minister lacked qualifications under New York Statutes: no congregation and not appointed by head of ecclesiastical order.</li>
<li><span class="PDFlink"><a href="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/RavenalvRavenal.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ulcseminary.org/forum/uploads/RavenalvRavenal.pdf" rel="nofollow">Ravenal v Ravenal (New York State)</a></span><span style="font-size:smaller;"><a href="/wiki/Portable_Document_Format" title="Portable Document Format">PDF</a>&#160;(3.56&#160;<a href="/wiki/Mebibyte" title="Mebibyte">MiB</a>)</span> Marriage annulled on basis ULC minister lacked actual church or stated meeting place.</li>
